149
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,376
{\fnSimHei}赏金猎人是拿尸首换钱{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}a bounty hunter deals in corpses.{\r}

150
00:15:59,543 --> 00:16:01,754
{\fnSimHei}帽子{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Hat.{\r}

151
00:16:05,507 --> 00:16:07,051
{\fnSimHei}干杯{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Prost.{\r}

152
00:16:15,225 --> 00:16:17,895
{\fnSimHei}州里提名悬赏人头{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}The state places a bounty on a man's head.{\r}

153
00:16:18,062 --> 00:16:20,731
{\fnSimHei}我追踪 锁定 然后了结他{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I track that man, I find that man, I kill that man.{\r}

154
00:16:20,898 --> 00:16:24,860
{\fnSimHei}了结他之后 我再把他的尸首运回去鉴定{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}After I've killed him, I transport that man's corpse back to the authorities.{\r}

155
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:27,738
{\fnSimHei}有时说比做可容易多了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Sometimes that's easier said than done.{\r}

156
00:16:27,905 --> 00:16:30,699
{\fnSimHei}我把尸首交给当局 确定一下{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I show that corpse to the authorities, proving yes, indeed,{\r}

157
00:16:30,866 --> 00:16:32,576
{\fnSimHei}我亲手杀死了他{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I truly have killed him,{\r}

158
00:16:32,743 --> 00:16:35,746
{\fnSimHei}然后当局再付给我相应的赏金{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}at which point the authorities pay me the bounty.{\r}

159
00:16:35,913 --> 00:16:39,249
{\fnSimHei}所以 就像奴隶买卖 人头换金钱{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}So, like slavery, it's a flesh for cash business.{\r}

160
00:16:40,876 --> 00:16:41,877
{\fnSimHei}什么是赏金?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What's a bounty?{\r}

161
00:16:45,673 --> 00:16:47,132
{\fnSimHei}就是奖赏{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}It's like a reward.{\r}

162
00:16:47,299 --> 00:16:50,678
{\fnSimHei}你杀人? 然后他们给你奖赏?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You kill people? And they give you a reward?{\r}

163
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:52,721
{\fnSimHei}某些人 对{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Certain people, yeah.{\r}

164
00:16:52,888 --> 00:16:54,014
{\fnSimHei}坏人?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Bad people?{\r}

165
00:16:54,181 --> 00:16:58,143
{\fnSimHei}对! 他们越坏 奖赏越多{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Ah! Badder they are, bigger the reward.{\r}

166
00:16:58,310 --> 00:17:00,604
{\fnSimHei}然后我就找上了你{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Which brings me to you.{\r}

167
00:17:00,771 --> 00:17:05,025
{\fnSimHei}我必须承认 对你呢 我有点进退两难{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And I must admit, I'm at a bit of a quandary when it comes to you.{\r}

168
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:07,611
{\fnSimHei}一方面 我鄙视奴隶制度{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}On one hand, I despise slavery.{\r}

169
00:17:07,778 --> 00:17:10,906
{\fnSimHei}另一方面 我实在需要你的帮助{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}On the other hand, I need your help.{\r}

170
00:17:11,073 --> 00:17:14,451
{\fnSimHei}如果你不持反对意见的话 那就太好了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}If you're not in a position to refuse, all the better.{\r}

171
00:17:15,327 --> 00:17:17,996
{\fnSimHei}所以 那时 我只能借奴隶买卖{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}So, for the time being, I'm gonna make this slavery malarkey{\r}

172
00:17:18,163 --> 00:17:20,374
{\fnSimHei}达到我自己的目的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}work to my benefit.{\r}

173
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:25,212
{\fnSimHei}不过 我已经说过了 我深感内疚{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Still, having said that, I feel guilty.{\r}

174
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:32,136
{\fnSimHei}因此 我想和你订个君子协议{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}So, I would like the two of us to enter into an agreement.{\r}

175
00:17:39,184 --> 00:17:41,019
{\fnSimHei}我在找布里托兄弟{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I'm looking for the Brittle Brothers.{\r}

176
00:17:45,691 --> 00:17:47,025
{\fnSimHei}但是 就算我再努力{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}However, at this endeavor,{\r}

177
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:52,322
{\fnSimHei}不知对方相貌 我显然占了下风{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I'm at a slight disadvantage insofar as I don't know what they look like.{\r}

178
00:17:53,574 --> 00:17:56,452
{\fnSimHei}但是你认得他们 对吧?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}But you do. Don't ya?{\r}

179
00:17:56,618 --> 00:17:58,829
{\fnSimHei}我是认得他们的长相{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I know what they look like all right.{\r}

180
00:17:58,996 --> 00:18:02,499
{\fnSimHei}好 我们就此协定{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Good. So here's my agreement.{\r}

181
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:06,086
{\fnSimHei}- 你陪同我 直到我们找到他们  - 我们去哪找?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- You travel with me until we find them.  - Where we goin'?{\r}

182
00:18:06,253 --> 00:18:08,881
{\fnSimHei}我听说他们其中至少两个在加特林堡做监工{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I hear at least two of them are overseeing up in Gatlinburg,{\r}

183
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:11,216
{\fnSimHei}但是我没有确切地点{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}but I don't know where.{\r}

184
00:18:11,383 --> 00:18:15,679
{\fnSimHei}所以我们要走遍加特林堡的农场去找{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}That means we visit every plantation in Gatlinburg till we find 'em.{\r}

185
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:21,101
{\fnSimHei}找到他们之后 你把他们指认出来 然后我来了结他们{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And when we find them, you point them out, and I kill them.{\r}

186
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:25,522
{\fnSimHei}你只要这么做 我就答应给你自由{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You do that, I agree to give you your freedom,{\r}

187
00:18:25,689 --> 00:18:29,818
{\fnSimHei}每个人头分你25块 一共75块{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}$25 per Brittle Brother. That's $75.{\r}

188
00:18:29,985 --> 00:18:33,697
{\fnSimHei}果然不出所料 警长来了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And, as if on cue, here comes the sheriff.{\r}

189
00:18:41,455 --> 00:18:46,960
{\fnSimHei}好啦 孩子们 闹够了吧 出来吧{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}OK, boys. Fun's over. Come on out.{\r}

190
00:18:49,588 --> 00:18:54,176
{\fnSimHei}好啦 都冷静{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}All right, folks, calm down.{\r}

191
00:18:55,219 --> 00:18:56,929
{\fnSimHei}都该干啥干啥去{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Go about your business.{\r}

192
00:18:57,721 --> 00:19:00,098
{\fnSimHei}这俩小鬼很快就上路了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}These jokers will be gone soon.{\r}

193
00:19:02,059 --> 00:19:07,481
{\fnSimHei}告诉我 为什么你们来我的镇子上惹麻烦?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Now, why y'all wanna come into my town and start trouble?{\r}

194
00:19:07,648 --> 00:19:10,901
{\fnSimHei}还吓坏了这些老实人{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And scare all these nice people.{\r}

195
00:19:12,069 --> 00:19:14,738
{\fnSimHei}你们就没点正经事做吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You ain't got nothing better to do{\r}

196
00:19:14,905 --> 00:19:18,116
{\fnSimHei}净来我比尔・夏普的小镇瞎捣乱{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}than to come into Bill Sharp's town{\r}

197
00:19:18,283 --> 00:19:20,536
{\fnSimHei}简直是自取其辱{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}and show your ass?{\r}

198
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:32,798
{\fnSimHei}你把我们警长怎么了?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What'd you just do to our sheriff?{\r}

199
00:19:44,101 --> 00:19:46,436
{\fnSimHei}你可以去叫司法官了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Now you can get the marshal.{\r}

200
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:50,274
{\fnSimHei}司法官! 司法官!{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Marshal! Marshal!{\r}

201
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,693
{\fnSimHei}- 我们要不要进去等?  - 咱们走吧?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- Should we wait inside?  - Can we just leave?{\r}

202
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:54,069
{\fnSimHei}你先请{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}After you.{\r}

203
00:19:56,530 --> 00:20:00,742
{\fnSimHei}把路对面的马车横着停边上 对着那家酒馆{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Move that buckboard a long ways across the street from the saloon.{\r}

204
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,787
{\fnSimHei}然后找六个人拿着来复枪蹲在车后面{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I want six men, six rifles behind it.{\r}

205
00:20:03,954 --> 00:20:06,123
{\fnSimHei}两个人拿着来复枪上这边房顶{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I want two men, two rifles up on this roof.{\r}

206
00:20:06,290 --> 00:20:08,625
{\fnSimHei}那边也上去两个{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Two men, two rifles on that roof.{\r}

207
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:11,753
{\fnSimHei}所有枪都指着那扇大门{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}All the barrels aimed at that front door.{\r}

208
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:14,923
{\fnSimHei}来人把可怜的比尔抬走{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Somebody get poor Bill outta the goddamn street.{\r}

209
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:18,260
{\fnSimHei}酒吧里的歹徒你听着!{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You in the saloon!{\r}

210
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:21,763
{\fnSimHei}你们已经被上百把来复枪包围了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}We got a hundred rifles aimed at every way out of that buildin'.{\r}

211
00:20:22,472 --> 00:20:25,642
{\fnSimHei}你们只有一次活着出来的机会{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You got one chance to get out of this alive.{\r}

212
00:20:26,476 --> 00:20:28,979
{\fnSimHei}你和你的黑鬼现在就弃械投降{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You and your nigger come out right now with your hands over your head,{\r}

213
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:31,106
{\fnSimHei}就现在{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}and I mean right now.{\r}

214
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:35,652
{\fnSimHei}是司法官大人亲自来接见我吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Is this the marshal I have the pleasure of addressing?{\r}

215
00:20:35,819 --> 00:20:37,613
{\fnSimHei}是的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yes, it is.{\r}

216
00:20:37,779 --> 00:20:39,865
{\fnSimHei}我是美国司法官吉尔・塔图姆{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}This is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.{\r}

217
00:20:40,032 --> 00:20:42,326
{\fnSimHei}无上荣幸 司法官大人{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Na wunderbar, marshal.{\r}

218
00:20:42,826 --> 00:20:46,413
{\fnSimHei}我已经正如你说的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I have relieved myself of all weapons,{\r}

219
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:49,499
{\fnSimHei}卸去了所有武器{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}and just as you have instructed,{\r}

220
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:52,336
{\fnSimHei}我正在以投降的姿态{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I am ready to step outside{\r}

221
00:20:52,502 --> 00:20:56,590
{\fnSimHei}向外面走来{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}with my hands raised above my head.{\r}

222
00:20:57,674 --> 00:21:00,093
{\fnSimHei}我相信我作为{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I trust as a representative{\r}

223
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:03,639
{\fnSimHei}美利坚合众国刑事司法体系的代表{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}of the criminal justice system of the United States of America,{\r}

224
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:09,645
{\fnSimHei}在上法庭之前是不可以被你和你手下{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I shan't be shot down in the street by either you or your deputies{\r}

225
00:21:09,811 --> 00:21:12,648
{\fnSimHei}乱枪打死在大街上的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}before I've had my day in court.{\r}

226
00:21:12,814 --> 00:21:15,150
{\fnSimHei}你是说不可以像你对警长那样{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You mean like you did our sheriff.{\r}

227
00:21:15,317 --> 00:21:17,110
{\fnSimHei}像条狗似的死在马路中央{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Shot him down like a dog in the street.{\r}

228
00:21:17,277 --> 00:21:19,613
{\fnSimHei}对 我就是那个意思{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yes, that's exactly what I mean.{\r}

229
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:25,452
{\fnSimHei}你能以执法者的名义承诺 不把我像狗一样射杀在马路中央吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Do I have your word as a lawman not to shoot me down like a dog in the street?{\r}

230
00:21:28,789 --> 00:21:32,042
{\fnSimHei}好吧 尽管我们都想把你格杀勿论{\r}
