268
00:24:34,474 --> 00:24:38,061
{\fnSimHei}反正我和我妻子信{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Oh, me and my wife do.{\r}

269
00:24:38,228 --> 00:24:42,399
{\fnSimHei}卡鲁肯老头不信 所以我们 呃... 跑了出来{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Old Man Carrucan didn't. That's why we, uh... we run off.{\r}

270
00:24:43,608 --> 00:24:45,235
{\fnSimHei}姜戈{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Django.{\r}

271
00:24:45,902 --> 00:24:48,488
{\fnSimHei}姜戈 姜戈{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Django, Django.{\r}

272
00:24:48,655 --> 00:24:51,366
{\fnSimHei}你胆子不小啊 姜戈{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You got sand, Django.{\r}

273
00:24:52,075 --> 00:24:53,952
{\fnSimHei}这个孩子胆子不小{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Boy's got sand.{\r}

274
00:24:55,745 --> 00:24:58,874
{\fnSimHei}我偏不喜欢有胆的黑鬼{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I got no use for a nigger with sand.{\r}

275
00:25:00,584 --> 00:25:04,087
{\fnSimHei}在他脸这儿烙个代表逃跑的r字{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I want you to burn a runaway "r" right here on his cheek.{\r}

276
00:25:04,254 --> 00:25:05,297
{\fnSimHei}那个女孩也烙上{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And the girl, too.{\r}

277
00:25:07,424 --> 00:25:12,220
{\fnSimHei}然后把他们带到格林维尔卖场上卖掉{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And I want you to take 'em to the Greenville auction and sell 'em.{\r}

278
00:25:13,054 --> 00:25:14,931
{\fnSimHei}两个都卖掉{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Both of 'em.{\r}

279
00:25:15,098 --> 00:25:16,850
{\fnSimHei}分开卖{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Separately.{\r}

280
00:25:19,311 --> 00:25:20,645
{\fnSimHei}这个嘛...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And this one...{\r}

281
00:25:23,273 --> 00:25:25,984
{\fnSimHei}我要你贱卖{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}you will sell him cheap.{\r}

282
00:25:27,944 --> 00:25:29,446
{\fnSimHei}在格林维尔...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}In Greenville...{\r}

283
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:34,951
{\fnSimHei}应该有个档案库{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}there should be some sort of a records office.{\r}

284
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:44,377
{\fnSimHei}记录着她什么时候被卖掉的...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You know when she was sold...{\r}

285
00:25:45,837 --> 00:25:48,798
{\fnSimHei}还有她从哪来{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}you know where she came from,{\r}

286
00:25:48,965 --> 00:25:50,800
{\fnSimHei}以及她的名字{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}and you know her name.{\r}

287
00:25:51,593 --> 00:25:53,136
{\fnSimHei}她叫什么来着?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What is her name?{\r}

288
00:25:53,303 --> 00:25:54,971
{\fnSimHei}布隆希达{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Broomhilda.{\r}

289
00:25:56,556 --> 00:25:59,809
{\fnSimHei}- 什么?  - 布隆 希达{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- What?  - Broom-hilda.{\r}

290
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:01,937
{\fnSimHei}- 布隆希达?  - 对的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- Broomhilda?  - Hm-mm.{\r}

291
00:26:04,022 --> 00:26:07,025
{\fnSimHei}- 她的主人是德国人?  - 对 你怎么知道的?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- Were her owners German?  - Yeah, how you know?{\r}

292
00:26:07,901 --> 00:26:09,319
{\fnSimHei}她不是在卡鲁肯农场出生的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}She wasn't born on the Carrucan plantation.{\r}

293
00:26:09,486 --> 00:26:12,030
{\fnSimHei}她被德国女主人养大 沙夫特家{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}She was raised by a German mistress, the Von Shafts.{\r}

294
00:26:12,197 --> 00:26:14,324
{\fnSimHei}她也会说一点德语{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}She speak a little German, too.{\r}

295
00:26:14,491 --> 00:26:16,243
{\fnSimHei}- 你妻子?  - 嗯{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- Your wife?  - Hm-mm.{\r}

296
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:18,245
{\fnSimHei}她还小的时候 女主人教过她{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}When she was little, her mistress taught her so she'd have somebody{\r}

297
00:26:18,411 --> 00:26:19,996
{\fnSimHei}为了能有个人说说话{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}to speak German with.{\r}

298
00:26:21,581 --> 00:26:24,167
{\fnSimHei}好了 我来理一遍{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Well, let me get this straight.{\r}

299
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:28,922
{\fnSimHei}你的奴隶妻子会说德语 而且她叫布隆希达・沙夫特?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Your slave wife speaks German and her name is Broomhilda Von Shaft?{\r}

300
00:26:29,089 --> 00:26:30,215
{\fnSimHei}对{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yep.{\r}

301
00:26:34,261 --> 00:26:37,013
{\fnSimHei}他们叫我希达{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}They call me Hildi.{\r}

302
00:26:49,261 --> 00:26:51,013
{\fnSimHei}田纳西州{\r}

303
00:26:53,697 --> 00:26:59,286
{\fnSimHei}进这些农场之后 我们要演场戏{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}When we gain access to these plantations, we'll be putting on an act.{\r}

304
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:03,373
{\fnSimHei}你有自己的角色要扮演{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You'll be playing a character.{\r}

305
00:27:10,255 --> 00:27:11,381
{\fnSimHei}怎么样?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Hm?{\r}

306
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:13,508
{\fnSimHei}不好看啊?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}No?{\r}

307
00:27:20,515 --> 00:27:24,978
{\fnSimHei}表演的时候 你不能出戏{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}During the act, you can never break character.{\r}

308
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:27,605
{\fnSimHei}你明白么?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Do you understand?{\r}

309
00:27:28,356 --> 00:27:30,900
{\fnSimHei}嗯 不出戏{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yeah. Don't break character.{\r}

310
00:27:33,236 --> 00:27:37,157
{\fnSimHei}你的角色就是随从{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And your character is that of The Valet.{\r}

311
00:27:37,907 --> 00:27:39,409
{\fnSimHei}什么意思?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What that is?{\r}

312
00:27:40,327 --> 00:27:42,704
{\fnSimHei}说不好听的就是仆人{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}That's a fancy word for servant.{\r}

313
00:27:42,871 --> 00:27:44,122
{\fnSimHei}- 随从?  - 嗯{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- Valet?  - Hm-mm.{\r}

314
00:27:45,623 --> 00:27:50,128
{\fnSimHei}现在嘛 姜戈 你可以为你的角色选戏服了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And now, Django, you may choose your character's costume.{\r}

315
00:27:52,547 --> 00:27:54,382
{\fnSimHei}你让我给我自己选衣服?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Youse gonna let me pick out my own clothes?{\r}

316
00:27:54,549 --> 00:27:55,508
{\fnSimHei}那是自然{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}But of course.{\r}

317
00:28:24,287 --> 00:28:25,497
{\fnSimHei}吁{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Whoa.{\r}

318
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:33,380
{\fnSimHei}在这里黑鬼骑马是犯法的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}It's against the law for niggers to ride horses in this territory.{\r}

319
00:28:33,546 --> 00:28:36,925
{\fnSimHei}他是我的随从 他不走路的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}This is my valet. My valet does not walk.{\r}

320
00:28:37,092 --> 00:28:40,970
{\fnSimHei}- 我是说在马上的这黑鬼...  - 他的名字是姜戈{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- I said niggers on horses...  - His name is Django.{\r}

321
00:28:41,137 --> 00:28:43,932
{\fnSimHei}他是自由的 他想骑什么就骑什么{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}He's a free man. He can ride what he pleases.{\r}

322
00:28:44,099 --> 00:28:47,560
{\fnSimHei}在我的地盘可不行 至少在我的黑鬼面前 不行{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Not on my property. Not around my niggers, he can't.{\r}

323
00:28:48,228 --> 00:28:53,233
{\fnSimHei}这位先生 我想我们误会了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}My good sir, perhaps we got off on the wrong boot.{\r}

324
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:55,860
{\fnSimHei}请容我解释{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Allow me to unring this bell.{\r}

325
00:28:56,027 --> 00:28:59,864
{\fnSimHei}我是金・舒尔茨医生 这是我的随从姜戈{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}My name is Dr. King Schultz. This is my valet, Django.{\r}

326
00:29:00,031 --> 00:29:02,158
{\fnSimHei}这是我们的坐骑托尼和小德{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And these are our horses, Tony and Fritz.{\r}

327
00:29:05,995 --> 00:29:07,372
{\fnSimHei}班尼特先生?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Mr. Bennett?{\r}

328
00:29:07,539 --> 00:29:11,751
{\fnSimHei}我听说您是一位绅士 也是位生意人{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I've been led to believe that you are a gentleman and a businessman.{\r}

329
00:29:11,918 --> 00:29:15,880
{\fnSimHei}因此我们才骑马从德州来到了田纳西州{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And it is for these attributes we've ridden from Texas to Tennessee{\r}

330
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:17,966
{\fnSimHei}与您会面{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}to parley with you now.{\r}

331
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:23,096
{\fnSimHei}我想从你这里买一个女奴{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I wish to purchase one of your nigger gals.{\r}

332
00:29:24,639 --> 00:29:27,725
{\fnSimHei}你和你的小喽从德州来到田纳西{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You and your Jimmie rode from Texas to Tennessee{\r}

333
00:29:27,892 --> 00:29:29,686
{\fnSimHei}就是为了买我一个女奴?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}to buy one of my nigger gals?{\r}

334
00:29:29,853 --> 00:29:31,521
{\fnSimHei}不事先打个招呼 啥也没有就来了?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}No appointment, no nothin'?{\r}

335
00:29:31,688 --> 00:29:33,606
{\fnSimHei}噢 的确如此{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Oh, I'm afraid so.{\r}

336
00:29:33,773 --> 00:29:36,192
{\fnSimHei}嗯 那如果我说我不喜欢你呢?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Well, what if I was to say I don't like you?{\r}

337
00:29:36,359 --> 00:29:38,027
{\fnSimHei}还有你的小丑黑鬼?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Or your fancy-pants nigger?{\r}

338
00:29:38,194 --> 00:29:40,405
{\fnSimHei}我什么都不打算卖给你{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And I wouldn't sell you a tinker's damn.{\r}

339
00:29:40,572 --> 00:29:42,532
{\fnSimHei}你想说什么吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Now what you got to say about that?{\r}

340
00:29:45,869 --> 00:29:47,787
{\fnSimHei}班尼特先生{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Mr. Bennett.{\r}

341
00:29:47,954 --> 00:29:51,207
{\fnSimHei}如果您真如传闻中说的那样具有商业头脑的话{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}If you are the businessman I've been led to believe you to be,{\r}

342
00:29:51,374 --> 00:29:56,546
{\fnSimHei}我有五千个理由可以改变您的想法{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I have 5,000 things I might say that could change your mind.{\r}

