{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What she do?{\r}

562
00:47:12,414 --> 00:47:13,874
{\fnSimHei}记不清了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I can't exactly remember.{\r}

563
00:47:14,041 --> 00:47:16,710
{\fnSimHei}反正就是违抗了他父亲的命令{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}She disobeys him in some way.{\r}

564
00:47:16,877 --> 00:47:20,047
{\fnSimHei}所以他把关在一座山的山顶{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}So he puts her on top of the mountain.{\r}

565
00:47:20,714 --> 00:47:21,840
{\fnSimHei}布隆希达在山里?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Broomhilda's on a mountain?{\r}

566
00:47:22,007 --> 00:47:23,258
{\fnSimHei}这是德国传说{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}It's a German legend,{\r}

567
00:47:23,425 --> 00:47:26,220
{\fnSimHei}总是有个山什么的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}there's always going to be a mountain in there somewhere.{\r}

568
00:47:26,386 --> 00:47:30,432
{\fnSimHei}他还安排了喷火龙守卫那座山{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And he puts a fire-breathing dragon there to guard the mountain.{\r}

569
00:47:32,100 --> 00:47:37,189
{\fnSimHei}用地狱之火围绕着她{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And he surrounds her in a circle of hellfire.{\r}

570
00:47:38,649 --> 00:47:42,986
{\fnSimHei}因此 布隆希达只好那么待着{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And there, Broomhilda shall remain.{\r}

571
00:47:44,279 --> 00:47:49,576
{\fnSimHei}除非有一位勇士能来拯救她{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Unless a hero arises brave enough to save her.{\r}

572
00:47:50,661 --> 00:47:52,246
{\fnSimHei}有么?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Does a fella arise?{\r}

573
00:47:52,412 --> 00:47:55,374
{\fnSimHei}有啊 姜戈 实际上 他真的去了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yes, Django, as a matter of fact, he does.{\r}

574
00:47:55,541 --> 00:47:57,584
{\fnSimHei}一个叫齐格弗里德的小伙子{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}A fella named Siegfried.{\r}

575
00:47:58,293 --> 00:47:59,294
{\fnSimHei}齐格弗里德救到她了吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Does Siegfried save her?{\r}

576
00:48:01,463 --> 00:48:04,091
{\fnSimHei}他做到了 很了不起{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Quite spectacularly so.{\r}

577
00:48:05,133 --> 00:48:09,263
{\fnSimHei}他爬上了大山 因为他无所畏惧{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}He scales the mountain, because he's not afraid of it.{\r}

578
00:48:09,972 --> 00:48:14,142
{\fnSimHei}他杀死了恶龙 因为他无所畏惧{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}He slays the dragon, because he's not afraid of him.{\r}

579
00:48:14,309 --> 00:48:16,812
{\fnSimHei}他穿越了地狱之火...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And he walks through hellfire...{\r}

580
00:48:19,147 --> 00:48:21,525
{\fnSimHei}因为布隆希达值得这么做{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}because Broomhilda's worth it.{\r}

581
00:48:25,654 --> 00:48:27,322
{\fnSimHei}我了解他的感觉{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I know how he feel.{\r}

582
00:48:28,782 --> 00:48:31,660
{\fnSimHei}我觉得我刚刚才了解到{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I think I'm just starting to realize that.{\r}

583
00:48:37,165 --> 00:48:41,336
{\fnSimHei}嗯 听着 姜戈...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Now, look, Django...{\r}

584
00:48:44,256 --> 00:48:48,302
{\fnSimHei}我毫不怀疑你会去拯救你的爱人...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I don't doubt that one day you'll save your lady love...{\r}

585
00:48:49,428 --> 00:48:53,015
{\fnSimHei}但我从心里不希望你去格林维尔{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}but I can't let you go to Greenville in a good conscience.{\r}

586
00:48:54,057 --> 00:48:58,520
{\fnSimHei}密西西比的奴隶市场可不适合你啊{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}A slave auction town in Mississippi isn't the place for you to visit.{\r}

587
00:48:58,687 --> 00:49:01,565
{\fnSimHei}不论你是不是自由人 那都很危险{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Free or not, it's just too dangerous.{\r}

588
00:49:04,526 --> 00:49:06,695
{\fnSimHei}让我来问你一个问题{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}But let me ask you a question.{\r}

589
00:49:14,202 --> 00:49:16,622
{\fnSimHei}你喜欢当赏金猎人吗?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}How do you like the bounty hunting business?{\r}

590
00:49:18,123 --> 00:49:20,459
{\fnSimHei}杀白人还有钱拿?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Kill white folks and they pay you for it?{\r}

591
00:49:21,293 --> 00:49:22,628
{\fnSimHei}怎么会不喜欢?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What's not to like?{\r}

592
00:49:22,794 --> 00:49:25,213
{\fnSimHei}我得承认 我俩搭档很不错{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Now, I have to admit, we make a good team.{\r}

593
00:49:25,380 --> 00:49:28,216
{\fnSimHei}我以为我杀了大约翰和小罗让你很不高兴呢{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I thought you was mad at me for killin' Big John and Lil Raj.{\r}

594
00:49:28,383 --> 00:49:30,469
{\fnSimHei}没错 那种场合下你是有点过分了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Yeah, on that occasion you were a tad overzealous,{\r}

595
00:49:30,636 --> 00:49:32,596
{\fnSimHei}不过一般来说 那也没什么{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}but normally, that's a good thing.{\r}

596
00:49:33,388 --> 00:49:35,599
{\fnSimHei}我们搭伙干一个冬天怎么样?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}How'd you like to partner up for the winter?{\r}

597
00:49:35,766 --> 00:49:37,768
{\fnSimHei}搭伙是什么意思?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}What you mean "partner up"?{\r}

598
00:49:37,934 --> 00:49:42,230
{\fnSimHei}整个冬天直到冰雪融化你跟着我...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You work with me through the winter till the snow melts...{\r}

599
00:49:43,231 --> 00:49:45,233
{\fnSimHei}奖金我分你三分之一{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I give you a third of my bounties.{\r}

600
00:49:46,443 --> 00:49:50,364
{\fnSimHei}我们这个冬天赚些钱 等雪化了{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}So we make some money this winter, and when the snow melts,{\r}

601
00:49:50,530 --> 00:49:53,450
{\fnSimHei}我亲自带你去格林维尔{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I'll take you to Greenville myself{\r}

602
00:49:53,617 --> 00:49:56,828
{\fnSimHei}我们去找你妻子的下落{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}and we'll find where they sent your wife.{\r}

603
00:50:01,083 --> 00:50:02,834
{\fnSimHei}你为什么这么关心我?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Why you care what happen to me?{\r}

604
00:50:04,586 --> 00:50:06,546
{\fnSimHei}为什么关心我是否找得到妻子?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Why you care if I find my wife?{\r}

605
00:50:06,713 --> 00:50:08,090
{\fnSimHei}坦白说...{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Frankly...{\r}

606
00:50:09,383 --> 00:50:12,260
{\fnSimHei}我从没有给过谁自由之身{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}I've never given anybody their freedom before.{\r}

607
00:50:12,427 --> 00:50:16,264
{\fnSimHei}现在我给了你自由 我觉得我对你负有一定的责任{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}And now that I have, I feel vaguely responsible for you.{\r}

608
00:50:17,516 --> 00:50:21,228
{\fnSimHei}再说 一个德国人遇到了现实中的齐格弗里德 没理由不帮一把的{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Plus, when a German meets a real life Siegfried, that's kind of a big deal.{\r}

609
00:50:23,772 --> 00:50:26,650
{\fnSimHei}作为一个德国人 我有义务帮你{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}As a German, I'm obliged to help you on your quest{\r}

610
00:50:26,817 --> 00:50:29,444
{\fnSimHei}拯救你的爱人布隆希达{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}to rescue your beloved Broomhilda.{\r}

611
00:52:38,740 --> 00:52:39,741
{\fnSimHei}注意点{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}You got her.{\r}

612
00:52:46,540 --> 00:52:51,461
{\fnSimHei}哦 杀白人挣钱先生 你怎么了?{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Ooh. What happened to Mr. "I Wanna Shoot White Folks For Money"?{\r}

613
00:52:51,628 --> 00:52:54,339
{\fnSimHei}- 他儿子也在那  - 嗯 很好{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}- His son's with him.  - Well, good.{\r}

614
00:52:54,506 --> 00:52:56,091
{\fnSimHei}他有个挚爱亲人在身边{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}He'll have a loved one with him.{\r}

615
00:52:56,258 --> 00:52:58,760
{\fnSimHei}也许还能留句遗言{\r}
{\fnCalibri\fs14\b0}Maybe even share a last word.{\r}

